{"parse":{"title":"British Video Association","pageid":26891160,"revid":834055994,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>The <b>British Video Association</b> (<b>BVA</b>) is a video home entertainment organisation established in 1980. Its members include the <a href=\"/wiki/BBC\" title=\"BBC\">BBC</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Cinema_of_the_United_States\" title=\"Cinema of the United States\">Hollywood studios</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> The Association organises an annual awards ceremony (The <i>BVA Awards</i>) in London.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In 2003, the BVA reported a 61% increase of <a href=\"/wiki/DVD\" title=\"DVD\">DVD</a> sales alongside a tripling in the illegal downloading of <a href=\"/wiki/Film\" title=\"Film\">film</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Television\" title=\"Television\">television</a> files.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In 2010 the Association publicised the fact that around six million people in the UK have failed to acquire a <a href=\"/wiki/HDTV\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"HDTV\">High Definition</a> signal for <a href=\"/wiki/HD_ready\" title=\"HD ready\">HD ready</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Television_set\" title=\"Television set\">Television sets</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=British_Video_Association&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Sophie Curtis (2 September 2013). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.telegraph.co.uk/technology/news/10281365/Broadband-providers-under-pressure-to-clamp-down-on-illegal-downloads.html\">\"Broadband providers under pressure to clamp down on illegal downloads\"</a>. <i>The Telegraph</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2 December</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Telegraph&amp;rft.atitle=Broadband+providers+under+pressure+to+clamp+down+on+illegal+downloads&amp;rft.date=2013-09-02&amp;rft.au=Sophie+Curtis&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Ftechnology%2Fnews%2F10281365%2FBroadband-providers-under-pressure-to-clamp-down-on-illegal-downloads.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABritish+Video+Association\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.eraltd.org/news/industry-news/bva-awards-2013.aspx\">\"BVA Awards 2013\"</a>. Entertainment Retail Association<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">9 January</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=BVA+Awards+2013&amp;rft.pub=Entertainment+Retail+Association&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.eraltd.org%2Fnews%2Findustry-news%2Fbva-awards-2013.aspx&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABritish+Video+Association\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\